<p>Suburban neighborhoods like Northeast Tacoma and Fern Hill offer ideal conditions for both solar and HVAC installations, with newer construction, optimal roof orientations, and fewer shading obstacles. The South End, including areas like Salishan and South Tacoma, provides excellent value opportunities for energy upgrades, with many homes benefiting significantly from high-efficiency systems. West End neighborhoods near Point Defiance may experience slightly different weather patterns due to proximity to Puget Sound, potentially affecting HVAC sizing requirements but offering consistent solar exposure.</p>

